                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Temporibus domni <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/87"
                            >Leoni</persName>
                        <rs key="#Popes">apostolici</rs>, pontificatus eius in Dei nomini anno
                        primo, | regnate domno <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79"
                            >Ugone</persName> et domno <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/72">Lothario</persName> filio eius magnis <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">regibus</rs>
                        <date>anno domni | Ugoni decimo et domni Lothari VI, die septimo mensis
                            ma(i)i, indictione VIIII</date>, in <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Vici">Lucoleta</placeName> infra <rs
                            key="#Plebs #Baptismal_churches">plebem</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs #Baptismal_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/74">Sancti
                            Iohannis</orgName> in <placeName key="#Vici #Plebs #Baptismal_churches"
                            ref="#places/27">Persecita</placeName>, <rs key="#City_territory"
                            >territorio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#City_territory" ref="#places/38">Motinense</placeName> vel
                            <placeName key="#City_territory #Plebs" ref="#places/7"
                            >Bononiense</placeName>. <rs key="#Commutatio">Commutant</rs> inter se |
                        presenti die domnus <persName
                            key="#Commutatio #Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Curtes #Fundi #Petiae #Count"
                            ref="#people/23">Bonefatius</persName>
                        <rs key="#count">comes</rs> filius bone memorie dom(ni) <persName
                            ref="#people/24" key="#Count">Ubaldi</persName> comitis, dans ipse
                        suprascriptus do(m)nu(s) | Bonefatius comes de iure suo in iure domni
                            <persName ref="#people/22"
                            key="#Commutatio #Curtes #Fundi #Petiae #Abbots">Ingelberti</persName>
                        venerabilis <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/47" key="#Curtes #Fundi #Monasteries"
                            >monasterii <placeName ref="#places/15" key="#Monasteries"
                                >Nonantule</placeName></orgName> territorio Moti|(ne)nsi eiusque
                        successoribus in perpetuis temporibus possidendum. Idest in <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundo</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Petiae #Maiores #Wine #Wood #Agricultural_workers #Other_minor_officer"
                            ref="#places/71">Gaiolo</placeName> omnibus rebus et casis qu(e) |
                        fuerunt recte et laborate per <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Geminianus/Paulicio">Geminiano</name> Paulicio</persName> et
                        modo fiunt laborate per <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Iohannes/Presurio">Iohanne</name> Presurio</persName> et
                        detinet | de ipsis rebus per infiteosin <persName><name ref="Berno"
                                >Berno</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Ursus/Paulicio"
                                >Urso</name> Paulicio</persName>, <persName><name ref="Azo"
                                >Azo</name></persName> et <persName key="#Other_minor_officer"><name
                                ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_minor_officer">dec(ani)</rs>, et sunt ipse res ad ratione |
                        facta int(er) <rs key="#Petiae">terra</rs>
                        <rs key="#Maiores">aratoria</rs> et <rs key="#Wine">vineata</rs> et terra
                        cum <rs key="#Wood">frascario</rs> iuge L et VI. Item in fundo<placeName
                            key="#Maiores #Petiae #Wine #Wood #Agricultural_workers #Houses #Fundi"
                            ref="#places/72">Viniole</placeName> | omnibus rebus et casis et vineis,
                        terris cum omni sua pertinentia int(er) terra aratoria et frascario et
                        vineata | ad ratione facta sunt iuges XVI et fiunt laborate ipse res per
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Samuel"
                                >Samuhelem</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannem</name></persName> et <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"
                                ><name ref="Petrus">Petrum</name></persName>; | simulque in fundo
                            <placeName
                            key="#Maiores #Petiae #Wine #Wood #Agricultural_workers #Houses #Forests #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fundi"
                            ref="#places/73">Riolo</placeName> omnibus rebus et casis, terris,
                        vineis, c[u]m omni sua pertinentia in integrum, quod est int(er) terra | de
                                <persName><name ref="Ismael">Hismahel</name></persName> et alia
                        terra cum <rs key="#Forests">silva</rs> et frascario, iuges XVII et habet
                        ibi <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">massaricia</rs> una que | fuit
                        recta et laborata per <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Andreas/Glutto">Andream</name> Glutto</persName> que habet
                        int(er) terra aratoria et vineata et silva|ta iuges XVIII. Et sunt de ipsis
                        rebus in <placeName key="#Fundi" ref="#places/74">Arcuado</placeName> iuges
                        IIIIor. E(t) est de suprascripis rebus in fundo | <placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Maiores #Wine #Wood #Casae/cassinae_massaricie"
                            >Rusti</placeName>, <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">massaricia</rs>
                        I, insimul cum terra aratoria et frascario et vineata ad ratione facta |
                        iuges XXVI in suprascripto fundo. Item in fundo <placeName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#places/75">Gavili</placeName> super totas omnes res meas et
                        pertinen|tias que ad nomen meum pertinent in suprascripto fundo aut in
                        circumiacentiis fundi[s] et modo | detinent per <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteusin</rs>
                        <persName key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Rainfredus"
                                >Rainfredus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petrus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                                >Adelbertus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Christinus">Cristini</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Daibertus"
                                >Daibertus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> et res | de <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Sigenulfus"
                                >Siginulfo</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Andreas"
                            >Andrea</name></persName>, item <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Priests"><name ref="Martinus"
                                >Martinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Leo"
                            >Leo</name></persName> et reliqui. Et in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/76">Gebolini</placeName>
                        massariciola | una que est iuges III. Itemque <placeName
                            key="#Petiae #Fiscal_property #Object" ref="#places/27">terra que
                            dicitur Regia</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Fiscal_property #Object">in fundo </rs><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#places/27">Persecetano</placeName> per singulas petiolas | mihi
                        pertinente ad ratione facta iuges XXX. Item in fundo <placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Maiores #Wood" ref="#places/82">Corticelle</placeName>,
                        terra aratoria | cum frascario quanta ibi habemus omnia in integrum, quod
                        est ad ratione facta iuges LXXV. | Et est ipsa res super totum insimul per
                        singula loca et fundoras sicut superius legitur iu[ges] | CCXLVII. Simulque
                        dans suprascriptus domnus Bonefatius comes de iure suo in iure domni
                        I[n]|gelberti venerabili abbatis monasterii Nonantule suisque successoribus,
                        idest omnibus rebus et casis iuris sui qu[e] | habere visus est trans <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvium Padum</rs> in locis et fundis seu casalibus que
                        dicitur <placeName key="#Fundi #Casalia">Fabrica</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Casalia" ref="#places/78">Badr[i]|niana</placeName> et in
                        pago <placeName key="#Pagus" ref="#places/77">Figariole</placeName> seu in
                        plebe de <placeName key="#Curtes #Plebs #Baptismal_churches"
                            ref="#places/79"><orgName key="#Plebs #Baptismal_churches"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/76">Septi Policino</orgName></placeName>
                        omnia in integrum quicquid invenire potueri|tis in ipsis suprascriptis
                        casalibus vel fundoras cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte mea que dicitur <geogName
                                key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/81">Septi Policino</geogName></rs> in
                            <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/84">Ferariense</geogName>, cum
                        omnia pertinentia que superius leguntur, que pertinet ad ipsam curtem cum
                        omnia super se et infra se habente sicut superius legitur in integrum, cum
                        terris, casis, edificiis, cispidibus, curtis, | hortis, areis, puteis,
                        aquis, rivis, rupinis aquarum, paludibus, piscacionibus, miscionibus,
                        venatio|nibus, arbustis, arboribus vel [animal]ibus a suprascritis rebus
                        mihi pertinentibus in suprascriptas fundoras | sicut superius legitur in
                        integrum. Et si amplius de ipsis rebus in suprascriptis locis inveneritis |
                        in vestro iure vestrorumque successorum permaneat. Et sunt ipse res insimul
                        super totum per singula | loca una cum ipsa curte cum suis pertinentiis et
                        apenditiis vel cum super se aut in[fra] | se aspicientibus iuges DCCCCXVIII.
                        Hec autem que superius leguntur temp[ore] | domni Ingelberti abbatis
                        translata sunt de breviario domni Bonifatii bone memorie | comitis causa
                        recordationis in breviari(um) sancte Nonantulensis ecclesiae. Et hec que |
                        sequuntur tra[n]slata sunt de breviario Nonantulensis ecclesie in breviarium
                        domni | Bonefatii bone memorie comitis. Dedit ipse suprascriptus venerabilis
                        Ingelbertus abbas monasteri Non[antule] | de iure ecclesie in iure domni
                        Bonefatii bone memorie comitis eiusque heredibus in perpet[uis tem]|poribus
                        possidendum curtem unam que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Wine #Oil #Chestnuts" ref="#estates/82"
                            >Funziano</geogName> in <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/83">Florentino</geogName> [in
                        lo]|co qui vocatur <placeName key="#Curtes #Wine #Oil #Chestnuts"
                            ref="#places/81">Maceline qui et Funziano</placeName> vocatus cum
                        omnibus rebus et pertinentiis su[is] | ad ipsam curtem pertinentibus una cum
                        casis et rebus illis que sunt posite in loco qui dicitur
                            <placeName>Sebe[..2..]no</placeName> et in loco que dicitur
                            <placeName>Susiano</placeName> et <placeName>Memuniano</placeName> vel
                        ubi et ubi infra suprascriptis com|itatibus ad ipsa curtem pertinentibus per
                        quovis titulum in integrum una cum terris, vineis, ca|sis, edificiis, seu
                        colonis et massariciis. Et hec sunt nomina illorum: <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Sigo">Sigo</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Lupus"
                            >Lupo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Albertus">Alperto</name></persName>, | <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Leopardus"
                            >Leopardo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Barantinus">Barantino</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Savinus"
                        >Savino</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Baruncius">Baruntio</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Giso">Giso</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Leopardo"
                                >Leopardo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"
                                ><name ref="Martinus">Martino</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Ildus">Ildo</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Lupus"
                            >Lupo</name></persName>, | <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Stefanus">Stephano</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Daibertus"
                            >Taiberto</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Teudebertus"
                            >Teoperto</name></persName>, item <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"
                                ><name ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Rotius">Rozo</name></persName> et
                        alio <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Ursus"
                            >Urso</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name
                                ref="Donatus">Donato</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Ursesredus"
                            >Ursesredo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"
                                ><name ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName> et alio <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Grimizus"
                                >Grimizo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Agricultural_workers"
                                ><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Agricultural_workers"><name ref="Ansulus"
                        >Ansulo</name></persName>. Istis suprascriptis residentibus in terra | que
                        pertinet de suprascript(am) curtem et est ipsa cors per apodismu(m) ad
                        rationem facta | iuges mil(le) CLXIIIor, et sunt tulpi <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vinearum</rs> in ea per num(erum) XXX, et tres | milia XXV una cum
                        silvis et <rs key="#Chestnuts">casteneto</rs> et <rs key="#Oil">oliveto</rs>
                        et pascuis, pratis, silvis, | salectis, arbustis, arboribus pomiferis,
                        fructiferis diversique generibus, aquis, rivis, | rupinis, usibus aquarum
                        fontibus, cultum et incultum cum omnia super se et infra se ha|bentem omnia
                        in integrum sicut superius comprehensum est ad ipsam curtem pertinentibus; |
                        et si amplius de ipsis rebus infra prenominata loca invenire potueritis in
                        vestro iure | permaneat.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
